Title: HP Pavilion 15-cs3065cl Home and Business Laptop (Intel i7-1065G7 4-Core, 32GB RAM, 256GB m.2 SATA SSD + 1TB HDD, Intel Iris Plus Graphics, 15.6" Touch Full HD (1920x1080) Win 10 Home) with USB3.0 Hub
HP Pavilion 15-cs3065cl Home and Business Laptop (Intel i7-1065G7 4-Core, 16GB RAM, 16GB Intel Optane + 1TB HDD, Intel Iris Plus Graphics, 15.6" Touch Full HD (1920x1080) Win 10 Home) with USB3.0 Hub
HP Pavilion 15-cs3065cl Home and Business Laptop (Intel i7-1065G7 4-Core, 32GB RAM, 2TB PCIe SSD, Intel Iris Plus Graphics, 15.6" Touch Full HD (1920x1080), WiFi, Win 10 Pro) with USB3.0 Hub
Review: The fan has been running loudly and constantly since the laptop was turned on. I have only been running Google Chrome and Adobe Acrobat (No gaming or high memory use type applications). When I took the computer to work in another room the battery drained within one hour (again not running an programs but work emails and typical work apps). This computer is supposed to have a ton of RAM and Memory and cost a lot of money so it is disappointing. My last HP lasted me years and was quiet and the battery lasted longer after multiple years of use using the same programs.
Review Rating: 2.0 out of 5 stars

HP ENVY Desktop Computer, Intel Core i7-9700, 16GB RAM, 1TB Hard Drive, 512 GB SSD, Windows 10 (TE01-0020, Black)
Review: My unit received was actually damaged from a forklift prong or similar bashing though the box and thus defective/inoperable, which should have never been delivered from the giant gash through box. But as a now 40 year techie I did get a chance to see what was inside, both motherboard, case design, components. These are F grade and you cannot re-purpose, reuse or replace. Hard drive was a thin ultra-cheap Seagate (never recommended, unethical to give this to people as a main hard drive!) Power unit was like 200-250 power range - just enough to power the ultra-low end build. DVD drive paper thin F grade. Wifi-bluetooth, USB hubs everything F Grade. Designed as cheap as possible. HP (and DELL) are both fill-in-blank today. If anything breaks (including the paper thin DVD drive), it cannot be replaced on basically either due to motherboard, psu and actual case design. Nor can it really be used with any rationality in another case. I imagine the cpu, ssd and ram are in fact in the only elements that are good and are going to be third-party, intel and samsung based parts. So why would someone spend the money when you are better off buying a better case, psu, media drive and motherboard and then your cpu/ram by a long long mile? Extremely unethical PC build designed to fill-in-the-blank computer shoppers. Shocking. What happened to these companies? Grade F- And I am serious F-. I hope this review really helps someone out and saves them imminent disaster or loss. People and companies should play fair, act honorably and nice to each other. HP no longer trusted with desktops- never again.,I am not a gamer so I do not use for online gaming. I do use this for my home office and after 3 laptops have an office space dedicated to work time. I paired this with a 34 lg ultra wide monitor. All I can say is Awesome. The ssd drive allows this to boot up more like an I pad than a pc. Its always ready to go I can run pandora and word and excel and surf the Internet or retrieve bank statements all at the same time and this baby doesnt slow or show me the circle of waiting. I highly highly recommend,Doesn't run hot like my 2012 HP Win 7 pc used to. Had a hard time locating the on button as it needs to protrude out more. When I tried to depress it at first nothing happened. Couldn't find the DVD player for days as everything is so concealed. Very sleek design. This is not a gaming pc as that's not what I was looking for. Bought extra powerful pc so won't have to upgrade later, hopefully. Very happy with it.,The HP Envy is exactly what I thought it should be. Very fast with calculations and applying the various programs that I installed. The inside is cramped, so if anyone wants to add memory (as I did) or to try to change the HDD to an SSD, it will be difficult.,The computer seemed ideal for one of my Building Automation Display computers. But, I had a few problems. In my application, the machine is required to run 24 hours a day on a UPS. This computer initially shut down every few days and had to be manually restarted. HP support came online and reinstalled the Windows 10 OS from scratch and this fixed that problem. In this application, I have to have two identical displays connected, running the same video. First I tried to do this by connecting one display in by the regular VGA port and the second (a touchscreen) via one of the USB ports. This words, BUT, every day or so, the "duplicate the same screen on both VGA displays" feature quits working for one or the other displays. I also tried just running the TWO displays from the ONE VGA port. Unfortunately, the VGA display port shuts down if you try to run two displays from the port.,This has plenty of power and memory for my Quickbooks software, plus I do lots of personal stuff on the internet, like shopping, email etc. I do not play any games so I have no idea if it's suited for that. It was not advertised as a gaming computer.,This product will not support any upgrades needed for graphics or gaming. The power supply is only 180w with proprietary wiring. Unable to add graphics card as power supply cannot support. HP technical support non existant, do not respond to questions on their website. I did find an obscure third party document saying that they can be upgraded which provided a part number for the power supply. Not available in the US, need to buy from Hong Kong. THis is not acceptable, HP need to support their customers, in my case Ex customer.,I think it was a refurbished computer because it came with a wireless mouse that doesn't work and there are no instructions as to how to put the battery in if it needs one, also the instructions refer to a wired mouse. The 8 pages of instructions that did come with it refer to page 11? the keyboard doesn't work properly and won't let me connect to the internet.

Title: Intel BOXNUC8i3CYSN1 NUC 8 Home, a Mini PC with Windows 10
Review: I purchased one of these NUCs to run retro video games in a HyperSpin arcade cabinet and it handles everything Ive thrown at it like a champ.,Works like it should. Don't let the numbers foold you. Even though the RAM and HD are high, the pc will lag even when not under stress. You neee atleast 8GB of RAM, because the pc will be using around 2 on idle. It does get the job done at the end of the day. It handles everyday task like docs, web surding, and youtube very well. There is a small buzzing noise which is quite noticible if you are close to it. All in all, if I wanted a gaming pc, I'd get something bigger like how it should be. I'd use this for small space and productive situations.,After 1st use the startup is slowing down,Tossed the (slow) HDD and 4gb RAM. Replaced with 1TB SSD and 32GB RAM. No complaints. I love the small form factor.,This is good product for watching youtube and browsing webs and decent games. You will need to add nvme ssd to prevent hypertension, this 1tb hdd is really slow.,Works as expected. Nice little machine.

Title: Intel NUC NUC10i7FNH Ultra Small Mini PC/HTPC - 10th Gen Intel 6-Core i7-10710U up to 4.70 GHz CPU, 8GB DDR4 RAM, 256GB SSD + 2TB HDD, Wi-Fi + Bluetooth, Intel UHD Graphics, Windows 10 Professional
Intel NUC NUC10i7FNH Ultra Small Mini PC/HTPC - 10th Gen Intel 6-Core i7-10710U up to 4.70 GHz CPU, 32GB DDR4 RAM, 2TB SSD, Wi-Fi + Bluetooth, Intel UHD Graphics, Windows 10 Professional
Review: This thing rocks. I purchased it to replace a tower that was approximately ten years old. It was quite easy to set up. A few tips: (1) the video port is hdmi, so if you have an older monitor, you may need to buy a converter, (2) it doesnt have a dvd drive, so if you have software on a dvd that you want to load, you will need an external dvd drive, (3) it doesnt have a lot of USB ports, and you will need some of them for your keyboard and mouse, so you may want to buy a hub, particularly if you will also be using an external dvd drive.,Sooo glad I got this. Just replaced my big desktop box, and this is faster, more storage, and about 1/50th the volume. Super easy setup... QSG not included because it's not needed.,After years of using computers this is the first time I enjoyed the speed of a computer may be because i bought 64Gb RAM and 1 TB SSD but its amazing I would write some of the things that can be improved although I love it as it is but these improvements can make it even greater.,Im using this as my proxmox homelab host and its incredible. Such amazing power and ram packed into a small box. Complete powerhouse. I run a dozen VMs and 6 containers and only using half the ram (32/64).,I specced an expensive NUC config to build out a streaming rig (separate from the gaming box) and was suffering a bit from sticker shock, when I found this unit. Same specs are at least $100 cheaper (and most of the time, more cheap) than non-amazon-prime sellers. That it was shipped via Prime was just cherry on top.,I know, it's corny, but after years of lugging around massive towers, this tiny PC does all the same work in a flash! Photoshop loads in seconds, batch reduces files in minutes, video rendering is about 4x realtime (14 minutes to render an hour-long HD video), and takes up minimal space on my desktop! I picked up a 12TB external drive for data storage, an external DVD drive for importing legacy video, and a docking station to give me plenty of additional ports.,I am a software developer so I need raw disk and CPU power (not video editing). I ordered the 64 GB model on 10/22/20 with a 10 day delivery estimate. They shipped FedEx overnight and it arrived on 10/24/20. That was a nice touch.,This product worked well for a month, its really fast and tiny. It started having issues like in 35 days, the monitors shut down suddenly and computer was still on. I then tried starting it by removing the power cord and pressing power button 2 times and then putting power cord back on and it started few times. Now it does not start at all. I dont recommend buying this product- My Toshiba laptop which is 8.5 years old still works which is windows 7. Its better to buy a Dell pc rather than to buy from a seller who might put substandard parts into this machine. I will try to repair it as I got warranty still on it and if that does not work then I will try to get refund. I am really upset with this purchase.
Review Rating: 5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,3.0 out of 5 stars

Title: Intel NUC NUC10i7FNH Ultra Small Mini PC/HTPC - 10th Gen Intel 6-Core i7-10710U up to 4.70 GHz CPU, 64GB DDR4 RAM, 512GB SSD, Wi-Fi + Bluetooth, Intel UHD Graphics, Windows 10 Professional
Review: I bought a NUC 10 with the goal of starting a simple home lab, this machine will be running VMs. Other users in the answers indicated they received a NUC with an NVMe SSD which would be ideal for a simple virtualization server.,Disappointed with the sellers equipment selection. Of course the series 10i7 chip is top notch, but found the two 8gB memories to be of the cheapest, slowest quality and mismatched by brand and speed. While it included a 500GB SSD, it did not make clear if it was sata or NVMe. What shipped was a low quality no-name SATA only available on eBay. As a result I will be replacing both the SATA and RAM with better quality items. Very miffed they would sell a top quality NUC and processor with junk components. I didn't expect the best ram and SSD, but these fall so far below as to be worthless.,The Intel NUC computer was shipped quickly and setup easily. While testing the computer I noticed that every component performed well except for the Solid State Drive (SSD). The benchmark software gave it a rating of 3925 which was equivalent to the worst SSD performance Ive seen in a decade. I checked the drive for errors and found none. The drive is just UNBELIEVABLY SLOW. It makes the computer perform poorly for many tasks (including booting).,My first NUC was an i5 with 8GB memory and 256GB SSD. My daughter has that one now (not sure how old).,This little box screams power especially coming from a 9 year old Toshiba laptop. Even though I upgraded it to a SSD and doubled the RAM, it is just not able to keep up, but this NUC 10, is like getting warp drive. I bought the 16gig of Ram and 512gig drive model and it turns on in seconds. Love it so far!,I've always had a PC connected to TV as an HTPC, browser, and occasional gamer. And along the way, I've had a lot of NUCs. The NUCs have something of a history in my house, sometimes being too noisy, too slow, too hot, or not good enough video. This one seems to have really nailed it, and for this price you get a solid system with Win10 Pro and some expansion room. I'm running everything 30' away with bluetooth keyboard+mouse. it is driving a 4k TV with no problem using a long-reach HDMI-over-fiber cable and an AV receiver in the middle.,This is the second Intel Nuc Mini Pc that I purchased and had to be returned because both were defective. I won't purchase this brand again.,purchased a new NUC 10th gen and I manage to mess up the hard drive. These guys gave me their number told me to call them and they were able to restore the hard drive for me. Extremely helpful! And the new computer is extremely kick ass! Thanks so much! - Cesar

Review: This is a very nice system if only it would stop over heating and crashing. Despite ensuring it is clear of all obstructions it still crashes at least once a week. I have my TV as the monitor but I am not able to get the full message when it overheats. If any one has a suggestion please help. UPDATE: Now the LAN stopped working and only WiFi is running. Sent in for repair and they switched out the drives then returned it, but some how UNREGISTERED all my software.,Totally disappointed in this product. Has 10th gen i7 intel chip and 64gb RAM, but still very slow. Extremely slow. Won't work with Razer and Sonnet eGPU enclosures with Vega 64 or 5700 XT graphic cards. I regret the purchase. If I had to do it all over again, I should have just put the money into a MacBook Pro 13 or 16.,Picked this up to build a new ESXi server for my home lab. Very quick system and I'm able to run about 10-12 virtual machines. Seller was super prompt and it arrive a day early.

Title: Intel NUC NUC10i7FNH Ultra Small Mini PC/HTPC - 10th Gen Intel 6-Core i7-10710U up to 4.70 GHz CPU, 16GB DDR4 RAM, 256GB SSD + 1TB HDD, Wi-Fi + Bluetooth, Intel UHD Graphics, Windows 10 Professional
Intel NUC NUC10i7FNH Ultra Small Mini PC/HTPC - 10th Gen Intel 6-Core i7-10710U up to 4.70 GHz CPU, 32GB DDR4 RAM, 1TB SSD, Wi-Fi + Bluetooth, Intel UHD Graphics, Windows 10 Professional
Review: This thing rocks. I purchased it to replace a tower that was approximately ten years old. It was quite easy to set up. A few tips: (1) the video port is hdmi, so if you have an older monitor, you may need to buy a converter, (2) it doesnt have a dvd drive, so if you have software on a dvd that you want to load, you will need an external dvd drive, (3) it doesnt have a lot of USB ports, and you will need some of them for your keyboard and mouse, so you may want to buy a hub, particularly if you will also be using an external dvd drive.,Sooo glad I got this. Just replaced my big desktop box, and this is faster, more storage, and about 1/50th the volume. Super easy setup... QSG not included because it's not needed.,After years of using computers this is the first time I enjoyed the speed of a computer may be because i bought 64Gb RAM and 1 TB SSD but its amazing I would write some of the things that can be improved although I love it as it is but these improvements can make it even greater.,Im using this as my proxmox homelab host and its incredible. Such amazing power and ram packed into a small box. Complete powerhouse. I run a dozen VMs and 6 containers and only using half the ram (32/64).,I specced an expensive NUC config to build out a streaming rig (separate from the gaming box) and was suffering a bit from sticker shock, when I found this unit. Same specs are at least $100 cheaper (and most of the time, more cheap) than non-amazon-prime sellers. That it was shipped via Prime was just cherry on top.,I know, it's corny, but after years of lugging around massive towers, this tiny PC does all the same work in a flash! Photoshop loads in seconds, batch reduces files in minutes, video rendering is about 4x realtime (14 minutes to render an hour-long HD video), and takes up minimal space on my desktop! I picked up a 12TB external drive for data storage, an external DVD drive for importing legacy video, and a docking station to give me plenty of additional ports.,I am a software developer so I need raw disk and CPU power (not video editing). I ordered the 64 GB model on 10/22/20 with a 10 day delivery estimate. They shipped FedEx overnight and it arrived on 10/24/20. That was a nice touch.,This product worked well for a month, its really fast and tiny. It started having issues like in 35 days, the monitors shut down suddenly and computer was still on. I then tried starting it by removing the power cord and pressing power button 2 times and then putting power cord back on and it started few times. Now it does not start at all. I dont recommend buying this product- My Toshiba laptop which is 8.5 years old still works which is windows 7. Its better to buy a Dell pc rather than to buy from a seller who might put substandard parts into this machine. I will try to repair it as I got warranty still on it and if that does not work then I will try to get refund. I am really upset with this purchase.

Title: Intel NUC NUC10i7FNH Ultra Small Mini PC/HTPC - 10th Gen Intel 6-Core i7-10710U up to 4.70 GHz CPU, 8GB DDR4 RAM, 1TB SSD, Wi-Fi + Bluetooth, Intel UHD Graphics, Windows 10 Professional
Review: This thing rocks. I purchased it to replace a tower that was approximately ten years old. It was quite easy to set up. A few tips: (1) the video port is hdmi, so if you have an older monitor, you may need to buy a converter, (2) it doesnt have a dvd drive, so if you have software on a dvd that you want to load, you will need an external dvd drive, (3) it doesnt have a lot of USB ports, and you will need some of them for your keyboard and mouse, so you may want to buy a hub, particularly if you will also be using an external dvd drive.,Sooo glad I got this. Just replaced my big desktop box, and this is faster, more storage, and about 1/50th the volume. Super easy setup... QSG not included because it's not needed.,After years of using computers this is the first time I enjoyed the speed of a computer may be because i bought 64Gb RAM and 1 TB SSD but its amazing I would write some of the things that can be improved although I love it as it is but these improvements can make it even greater.,Im using this as my proxmox homelab host and its incredible. Such amazing power and ram packed into a small box. Complete powerhouse. I run a dozen VMs and 6 containers and only using half the ram (32/64).,I specced an expensive NUC config to build out a streaming rig (separate from the gaming box) and was suffering a bit from sticker shock, when I found this unit. Same specs are at least $100 cheaper (and most of the time, more cheap) than non-amazon-prime sellers. That it was shipped via Prime was just cherry on top.,I know, it's corny, but after years of lugging around massive towers, this tiny PC does all the same work in a flash! Photoshop loads in seconds, batch reduces files in minutes, video rendering is about 4x realtime (14 minutes to render an hour-long HD video), and takes up minimal space on my desktop! I picked up a 12TB external drive for data storage, an external DVD drive for importing legacy video, and a docking station to give me plenty of additional ports.,I am a software developer so I need raw disk and CPU power (not video editing). I ordered the 64 GB model on 10/22/20 with a 10 day delivery estimate. They shipped FedEx overnight and it arrived on 10/24/20. That was a nice touch.,This product worked well for a month, its really fast and tiny. It started having issues like in 35 days, the monitors shut down suddenly and computer was still on. I then tried starting it by removing the power cord and pressing power button 2 times and then putting power cord back on and it started few times. Now it does not start at all. I dont recommend buying this product- My Toshiba laptop which is 8.5 years old still works which is windows 7. Its better to buy a Dell pc rather than to buy from a seller who might put substandard parts into this machine. I will try to repair it as I got warranty still on it and if that does not work then I will try to get refund. I am really upset with this purchase.

Title: Intel NUC 10 Performance Kit  Intel Core i7 Processor (Tall Chassis)
Review: Configured with:,I'm happy with the size and build quality of this device.,Zippy and quiet just what I needed. Creating a home lab with a type 1 hypervisor I have an ESXi 6.7 key so I will most likely go that route. Bought a second to mess around with not sure what OS but I put ubuntu 19.10 on this, for now, was up in less than an hour. I went this route for ease of use and was not disappointed. 12 threads so its seen as 12 cores @ 1.8mhz. 64GB 32X2 Samsung 2666, 1 nvme 1TB Samsung 970 evo+ m.2 all this is on the approved vendor list so no compatibility issues. Seems like it will make a solid platform to practice real-world virtualization. I was going to build an threadripper server but decided to go more modular.,This nuc is awesome. I bought it to replace a functioning macmini that was not performing as fast as I needed. I was tired of apple's immoral lock-in practices and decided to go back to building my own system that supports running Linux. The hardware is great. I7 CPU is very fast along with all the other attached module. WIFI bluetooth etc... I am running 3 displays with no problems. I maxed out the nuc to the fullest which is 64GB of ram and I was still under $1k with hard-drive + ram. Very great value for the money. I will be buying nucs as my main computer moving forward. The form factor is perfect for my desk. Small but packs tons of power + speed,When installing Linux Mint 19.3 on this I ran into one issue, networking did not work. The kernal included with 19.3 does not support Ethernet, either with a cable or WiFi. It turned out there is a more recent kernal available for download. Amazon will not let me post the links in this review, but the solution is searchable on the Linux Mint forum with instructions on how to easily update the kernal.,WD SN550 1tb

Intel NUC 8 Mainstream Kit (NUC8i5BEK) - Core i5, Short, Add't Components Needed
Review: The problem with i7 nucs is that they are small, but not silent. This generation does not fix it. For all the usual tasks, like watching youtube, doing office work or really light gaming, it is quite and stays around 40 C. But if you were hoping to use its i7 to its full potential, be prepared for the nuc to hit 85 degrees with irritating fan noise.,I had the NUC7i5BNH but sold it due to the constant fan noise or coil whine which was really annoying. I recently bought the NUC8i5BEK and I can state that it is very quiet compared to the previous (7th gen.) model. Intel finally listened to consumers and put a better cooling system into the NUC for the 8th gen. CPUs. Also, the Core i5-8259U is a much stronger CPU than the previous i5-7260U.,Works out of the box with Proxmox VE and Ubuntu 18.04. On-board NIC not currently compatible with ESXi 6.7.,This review is for the BOXNUC8i5BEH1, the "tall" i5 "kit" that does not include RAM or HDD. (Note that i3, i5, and i7 reviews are unhelpfully combined here, unless you know how to filter the reviews.)

Title: Intel NUC8I5BEK Mini PC NUC Kit - 8th Gen Intel Quad-Core i5-8259U Processor up to 3.80 GHz, 64GB DDR4 Memory, 2TB NVMe Solid State Drive, Intel Iris Plus Graphics 655, Windows 10 Pro (64-bit)
Intel NUC 7 Business Kit (NUC7i3DNKH1E) - Core i3, Tall, Add't Components Needed
Review: This NUC is what it says: an Intel NUC. The CPU is correct, as are the ram and m.2 slots. The ports also seem to be correct, mostly. The machine boots, and seems to work just fine. In fact, I'm typing this review on it.,For size and performance it doesn't get any better than this!!!! I'd give it 10 stars if I could. IT SIMPLY ROCKS!!!! Smallest PC on the market. Produces 4K@60Hz with ease. I build 3 PC 's a year and this is one the few that I didn't have to sort newer drivers for fix minor issues. This worked out of the box with the addition of Win 10 Pro OS, 16GB SODIMM RAM and 500GB NVMe M.2 . The PC offers every control option and custom tuning of the CPU fan to make it near silent....BUT newbies be aware that setting your fan parameters incorrectly will cook your processor.,Perfect ones.,I'm used to using the NUC7i3BNK but this one had same day delivery and I needed 3 of them quickly. These are used for basic office use, I put a 128GB M.2 SSD in them (I load the images on them through a USB adapter using Acronis True Image), 8GB of RAM and Win10Pro licenses. Been using the NUCs for this purpose for 3 generations now with no issues.,I bought two of these to extend a test cluster for my home lab. They both came sealed in new packaging. After plugging in a M.2 SSD and a 16GB stick of RAM, they booted via USB fine. I have them stacked up under my desk now (they have rubber feet that allow a few to sit on top of one another -- I wouldn't stack more than 4 or 5 of them tho). It would be nice to have vPro support on these (it doesn't), but I can't complain given the price.,Really nice mini to build all in one solutions with on backs of large or small monitors.,This is a perfect Mini-Server. I use it to host a CentOS Environment for developing websites. It's faat, quiet and just perfect for what I need.,Shop guys custom made the "L" bracket and made plate to hang NUC pc.

Intel NUC 8 Mainstream Kit (NUC8i3BEH) - Core i3, Tall, Add't Components Needed
Review: The problem with i7 nucs is that they are small, but not silent. This generation does not fix it. For all the usual tasks, like watching youtube, doing office work or really light gaming, it is quite and stays around 40 C. But if you were hoping to use its i7 to its full potential, be prepared for the nuc to hit 85 degrees with irritating fan noise.,I had the NUC7i5BNH but sold it due to the constant fan noise or coil whine which was really annoying. I recently bought the NUC8i5BEK and I can state that it is very quiet compared to the previous (7th gen.) model. Intel finally listened to consumers and put a better cooling system into the NUC for the 8th gen. CPUs. Also, the Core i5-8259U is a much stronger CPU than the previous i5-7260U.,Works out of the box with Proxmox VE and Ubuntu 18.04. On-board NIC not currently compatible with ESXi 6.7.,This review is for the BOXNUC8i5BEH1, the "tall" i5 "kit" that does not include RAM or HDD. (Note that i3, i5, and i7 reviews are unhelpfully combined here, unless you know how to filter the reviews.)
Review Rating: 4.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,4.0 out of 5 stars

Intel BOXNUC5CPYH NUC PC with Intel Celeron N3050
Review: Remember the last time you thanked yourself for purchasing an Intel Celeron Processor? Probably never happened. If you buy this NUC version, you won't be thanking yourself either. Ran this guy with 8GB RAM and an SSD. Results were, initially , palatable. I had to retire this NUC and get the next version up, which is worth the extra money. Streaming HD was choking. I thought it might be the wifi, the bandwidth, something.. turns out the CPU just gets maxed out all the time. I was running a lite version of Linux, but Chrome and Firefox browsers would bring this system to its knees. Perhaps all the kerfuffle and patching with the Intel processors really made the CPU performance of this model unacceptable in 2018 and beyond.,Purchased this (along with an Samsung 850 EVO 120GB SSD and Kingston 8GB SODIMM) to replace an aging home-built midtower HTPC in a bedroom, with the intention of using it pretty much strictly for Kodi, Amazon Instant Video, and a Steam streaming box. Because of this I opted for a Linux install as Windows would be overkill. I prefer Windows but am familiar enough with Linux that it was little trouble.,I equipped mine with 4GB of Ram and a 120GB ssd. OS is Win 10 Home.,This NUC is a well-priced, low-powered machine perfect for office drones or media centers. Its GPU includes hardware acceleration for not just H.264 (AVC) but also H.265 (HEVC). Total system power consumption is very low, but it includes a 65-watt switch-mode brick which is nice. Windows 10 support is very good, and Windows Update contains drivers for all system hardware which is convenient.
Review Rating: 2.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,4.0 out of 5 stars

Title: Intel NUC NUC8I7HVK Mini PC, Intel QuadCore i7-8809G Upto 4.2GHz, 16GB DDR4, 512GB NVMe SSD, AMD Radeon RX Vega M GH, WiFi, Thunderbolt 3, 4k Support, Windows 10 Pro (16GB Ram + 512GB SSD)
Review: bought this for my son after watching many videos showing how amazing this mini pc is. after trying to set it up, we realized how much of a real rip off it is. We bought the 32gb and 512 ssd model which comes with both already installed. My son is a gamer so he wanted to play fortnite/ rainbow six siege. both wouldn't launch saying the graphics card did not reach the requirement or it needed to be upgraded. We went to the intel driver site and that was an even bigger pain to install. Over all, very very bad product, all of the other good reviews are fake. Trust me on this, do not buy the product.,i order the 32g ram / 512g ssd combo,The only reason I'm giving this 3 stars is I do not like false "bait & switch" offerings since the internal SSD was not what was advertised as a 2TB Samsung 970 NVMe. I installed a 2nd 2TB Samsung 970 NVMe and when I opened the NUC8I7HVK up, what I found in the other slot was a 2TB Intel 660p which I've pictured. Although the Intel is slower than the Samsung in benchmark transfer speed & therefore costs less, it probably will not be noticeable. Its just the fact that some of the lower star reviews also mentioned that they didn't get the stated brand of components makes this seller on my "buyer beware" list. I even posted a question to the seller if they could install a 2nd 2TB Samsung Evo NVMe but they couldn't as it had already been shipped. I'm glad they didn't as I probably would have gotten two Intel 660p or maybe even less. Other than that, the rest of the components, OS and processor were correct, it does run fast as expected. I use for multitasking (no gaming) and its hooked up to the new LG Ultrawide 49WL95C-W monitor. The small form factor was perfect must since the monitor takes up most of the desk.,This thing is so lame. I don't know why it is but it is! I purchased 3 of these from the same people and that in and of itself was a mistake.The sound almost never works. There is ALWAYS work to do if I want sound. Video playing is ridiculous. I get more error messages while running video (mostly basic mp4). I have and alwas have had much difficulty with mp4s, both locally as well as streaming like youtube. Intel dropped the ball on this mini PC because I have so many problems and I have the troubles on both of thes HVK models. The HNK one seems to be working fine for my wife because she hasn't complained. Both HVK models are using large tv screens as their one and only monitor. Both TVs are newer 4k models. I thought it might be that but I ran a regular monitor and no change besides, I would think Intel has long solved TV's, HDR etc.. My arrangement is common nowadays. The seller could not have cared any less about my problems and never helped me one iotta and never followed up with me...NEVER!! I would NOT buy a NUC again and will not give this merchant my return business no matter what and that is what I recommnend for other buyers... unless you are really good and don't mind a bit of trouble and need no assistance (support) from the seller. If you can make it past those glaring shortcomings then break out the cc and go for it!,Received my NUC and works great, but! one issue that will not go away no matter what I try and that is the driver for the tps65988 USB power port will not update, I have used Intels update site but the driver never corrects the problem. I've search the web for answers but no one seems to have corrective actions on this issue. So I have to give this a low rating on the system not the seller.,It's awesome! I don't use this for gaming, so this might not be the review for you. I use this for work as a laptop alternative as it's size is very portable. The power supply is nearly as big as the PC and is difficult to find a spare. Intel is giving me the run around. Apparently it's not a very common request as a spare part. Otherwise it is incredibly fast for every task I use it for and the connectivity is awesome.,UPDATE: DON't BUY THIS! After returning I bought this from another seller and had problems with it the whole time until now, a year and a half later. Now it's died completely. POS For this amount of money I expected a top quality product that would last many years!,Here's what you need to know about this machine before you buy it:

Intel NUC 8 Performance-G Kit (NUC8i7HVK) - Core i7 100W, Add't Components Needed
Review: Seeing that I've had the NUC8i7HVK (8809G) for 2 months now I decided I should probably write a review on it. Note that I had previously been using an AMD R2400g system I had built for my wife. Unfortunately, no matter what I tried with the 2400g I just could not get it to be stable while gaming. I spent two months troubleshooting every possible piece of hardware/software and finally just gave up and got the Hades Canyon NUC. Immediately I had a better experience with the NUC.,,Awesome little machine packed with incredible power. It is running VR alright but you can feel it is maxing out its capacity. There is no room for more. Added 32Go Corsair DRAM and two SSD PCie Samsung 970. So overall a pretty expensive configuration. It is running pretty silently for me most of the time (except for VR).
Review Rating: 5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,4.0 out of 5 stars

Review: Excellent laptop! Comes with Windows 10 Pro. I put Linux on mine w/o any trouble. I can revert back to Windows if I choose to however it works well with Linux Mint. Powerful and sturdy. Quite happy with it so far.,Love this laptop! The Ryzen 7 processor is super fast! I was extremely easy to setup and needed very few OS updates. Excellent value for the price. 16mb RAM and 256gb hard drive.,Would of given 5 stars BUT battery life is horrible. Have to purchase all programs separately. No backlight keyboard, which I thought it had? Still learning to use and purchased to work on the go. It is a great laptop but battery runs low after 4 hrs or so.,The laptop is surprisingly light for a 15 inch laptop and has great specifications. I love the track point and the keyboard is solid. The display is also great. The speakers are decent, but not its strongest point. Overall, this laptop does all of the important things right and comes in at a good price.,I was concerned about the AMD processor as I had never owned one before. Turned out be a non-issue, amazing performance.,Love this laptop. Fast and easy to use.
Review Rating: 5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,3.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars

Review: I own over 55 Lenovo laptops, I ordered 4 of these, soon as I got the shipment I knew there was a problem; someone had placed another seal over the anti-tamper Lenovo seal, the laptop itself was not in the original Lenovo wrapper, and there were no Lenovo programs installed on it, and the computer name was DESKTOP-DUMS8VA, all Lenovo laptops have their name, and these are not desktops. So this must have been a return, reject, or whatever.,This laptop came quickly and was in perfect condition has been working great. Awesome laptop overall. If I need more tech I wont hesitate buying from this seller in the future.,Purchased for an accountant who insisted on a numeric keypad with normal-sized keys. (The few inexpensive laptops you might see at Best Buy tend to have skinny keys that she deemed useless for significant data entry.) It has a very pleasing look and weight, the black plastic is sleek and nice.
Review Rating: 1.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars

Review: I had a 12 year old HP EliteBook 8570p of which due to TPM chip being locked in BIOS I was starting to have MS login issues with Outlook, Teams, etc. So being I haven't purchased a good powerful notebook in a while I figured it's time for an upgrade so I can get work done easier as well as for personal use. Since I have booted up this new laptop nothing but performance and ease of use. And it also works with my slim docking station as well. I just hope that this EliteBook last another 12 years like my last one. Early to tell right now, but so far it was worth the price. Oh and the old notebook is still good, just having some TPM issues with MS products.
Review Rating: 5.0 out of 5 stars

Title: 2019 Newest HP Elitebook 850 G6 15.6" Full HD FHD(1920x1080) Business Laptop (Intel Quad-Core i7-8565U Vpro, 32GB DDR4 RAM, 1TB PCIe NVMe SSD) Fingerprint, Backlit, Thunderbolt, B&O, Windows 10 Pro
Review: I bought this around Thanksgiving time. The delivery was fast as promised. Unfortunately, this is the only thing that went right. The laptop Blue Screened upon first use and continued to Blue Screen. I tried to reach the seller, they responded once and asked for the error code on the Blue Screen. I responded the Blue Screen flashes so fast I cannot read the error code. I asked for additional help and to date have not received a response. Really lousy they cannot be bothered to respond to a $1,400 plus purchase!,This computer is SUPER FAST! After completing the setup, it boots up in seconds. The processor speed runs as fast as a high end desktop PC. I just ran a WiFi Speed Test. The results: Download Speed 230 Mbps, Upload Speed 28.2 Mbps (with the laptop being about 30 feet away from the Router on the other side of the house) so the WiFi adapter runs very high speed WiFi. The M.2 PCIe NVMe SSD (Solid State Drive) is the FASTEST and most RELIABLE hard drive you can buy in a laptop! I like the sleek, slim, silver design of the HP chassis. The laptop carries the original HP manufacturer's warranty. Shipping was FAST. Overall, I would HIGHLY RECOMMEND this excellent computer!,I thought tge computer was amazing at first. But I quickly found out that the computer crashes and restarts after about watching 3 minutes into a video....... im extremelyrics angry about this.,Awesome laptop. Light weight, slick form factor and fast. Perfect for coding anywhere. Plus the speakers are great too.
Review Rating: 1.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,2.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars

Review: I needed a new laptop for my small business because the one I owned was so slow and continued to freeze when opening programs while working with my clients. This laptop is so fast at start up and has continued to run smoothly since I've had it. It has taken so much stress out of my day to say because it works so seamlessly. It is worth every dollar.,Good bang for the buck. Extremely fast with all the features you could ever want without the cost of some of the other brands. It will keep up with whatever you throw at it.,Kept freezing from day 1. Eventually i sent it to Lenovo for warranty repair. They found "UNIT HAS A 3RD PARTY SSD THAT IS CAUSING CX ISSUE. TO RESOLVE ISSUE CX SHOULD REPLACE WITH LENOVO SSD." I dont even know if they sold me a Lenivi or some fake garbage,I have had this laptop for 3 weeks now and its been great. It starts up quickly and runs all the programs efficiently. Im very pleased with all it has done so far.,It arrived quickly and with all of its components -- beautiful, sleek and fast machine!

Review: Was a fair bit skeptical given that this product came with a non standard amount of RAM, but who can pass up 24gb for the price of the regular device? I was also in dire need of a laptop replacement since my old one died, but alas...,Hands the best purchase Ive made in the last year. This 8 core processor is amazing! Everything is blazing fast and the extra ram helps a ton!,I bought another one at the store and it's very nice.,It's a performance monster. Works like a charm. Only issue is when you're putting in performance mode, the fans tend to get loud and it can get pretty hot. But that's if you max out the graphics and processor.,Great everyday laptop that can also game. The track pad and display have really been standing out to me (1080p version). Battery life is great, and has differebt battery settings to help it have an extended life. 65w USB-C charging is handy, only need one charger for cellphone, laptop and buds. Definitely happy with this purchase and would recommend it to most. Please note that there is no webcam in this computer, I think that's a pro but others may think is a con.
Review Rating: 4.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars,4.0 out of 5 stars,5.0 out of 5 stars
